<subSubSection id="AAB96554A666FF8948DDBB5BB9A5F928" pageId="6" pageNumber="145" type="etymology">
<paragraph id="E21C36DFA666FF8948DDBB5BB9A5F928" blockId="6.[189,813,1561,1790]" pageId="6" pageNumber="145">
Etymology. The specific name is a present participle taken from Latin and refers to the stridulatory apparatus on the femora Iand carapace of most 
<taxonomicName id="25A34D5CA666FF8949DFBB87B9B9F928" authorityName="Petrunkevitch" authorityYear="1928" box="[504,655,1711,1731]" class="Arachnida" family="Salticidae" kingdom="Animalia" order="Araneae" pageId="6" pageNumber="145" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="subFamily" subFamily="Heliophaninae">Heliophaninae</taxonomicName>
.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection id="AAB96554A666FF8948DDBBE5BE91FAB7" pageId="6" pageNumber="145" type="diagnosis">
<paragraph id="E21C36DFA666FF8948DDBBE5BE91FAB7" blockId="6.[189,813,1561,1790]" lastBlockId="6.[850,1475,1293,1790]" pageId="6" pageNumber="145">
Diagnosis. Male of this species can easily be recognized by very long embolus, arising proximally from the retrolateral side of the tegulum and having a retrolateral loop on its tip (
<figureCitation id="7A982A5AA666FF894D54B825BE80FACA" box="[1395,1462,1293,1313]" captionStart="Figures 15-20" captionStartId="6.[189,256,1173,1193]" captionTargetBox="[352,1306,201,1167]" captionTargetId="figure@6.[344,1309,189,1172]" captionTargetPageId="6" captionText="Figures 15-20. Left palp of (15-16) Helvetia galianoae: (15) ventral view̡ (16) retrolateral view; (17-18) Helvetia humillima: (17) ventral view̡ (18) retrolateral view; (19-20) Helvetia stridulans: (19) vental view̡ (20) retrolareal view. Bars = 0.25 mm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.3678513" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/3678513/files/figure.png" pageId="6" pageNumber="145">Fig. 19</figureCitation>
). This is also the only known species that has a ventral branch more developed than the dorsal branch of the RTA (
<figureCitation id="7A982A5AA666FF894D70B860BEAAFAB7" box="[1367,1436,1352,1372]" captionStart="Figures 15-20" captionStartId="6.[189,256,1173,1193]" captionTargetBox="[352,1306,201,1167]" captionTargetId="figure@6.[344,1309,189,1172]" captionTargetPageId="6" captionText="Figures 15-20. Left palp of (15-16) Helvetia galianoae: (15) ventral view̡ (16) retrolateral view; (17-18) Helvetia humillima: (17) ventral view̡ (18) retrolateral view; (19-20) Helvetia stridulans: (19) vental view̡ (20) retrolareal view. Bars = 0.25 mm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.3678513" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/3678513/files/figure.png" pageId="6" pageNumber="145">Fig. 20</figureCitation>
).
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection id="AAB96554A666FF894BA8B84EBF79F915" pageId="6" pageNumber="145" type="description">
<paragraph id="E21C36DFA666FF894BA8B84EBE38F90A" blockId="6.[850,1475,1293,1790]" pageId="6" pageNumber="145">
Description. Male (holotype). Total length: 3.40. Carapace brown, 1.60 long, 0.90 wide, 0.55 high, with white scales laterally. Cephalic area black. Ocular quadrangle 0.75 long. Anterior eye row 0.85 wide and posterior 0.80 wide. Chelicera dark brown. Endite, labium and sternum brown. Palp as in figures 19 and 20. Legs 4132, I black, with femur and patella brown, II-IV whitish with few brown stripes. Length of femur: I 0.65, II 0.60, III 0.65, IV 0.85; patella + tibia: I 1.05, II 0.70, III 0.70, IV 1.00; metatarsus + tarsus: I 0.55, II 0.50, III 0.70, IV 0.80. Spination. Femur I, II, III, IV d1-1-1; tibia I 0, II 
<date id="961D101FA666FF894C48BB5CBFB2F96C" box="[1135,1156,1652,1671]" pageId="6" pageNumber="145">v1</date>
pr, III 0, IV 
<date id="961D101FA666FF894CD9BB5CBE22F96C" box="[1278,1300,1652,1671]" pageId="6" pageNumber="145">v1</date>
-0-2; metatarsus I 
<date id="961D101FA666FF894B75BBB9B8B6F94F" box="[850,896,1681,1700]" pageId="6" pageNumber="145">v2-2</date>
, 
<date id="961D101FA666FF894BAEBBBAB893F94F" box="[905,933,1681,1701]" pageId="6" pageNumber="145">II 1</date>
rpr, III p1di, r1di, IV 
<date id="961D101FA666FF894C53BBB9BFBBF94E" box="[1140,1165,1681,1701]" pageId="6" pageNumber="145">v2</date>
di, p1di, r1di. Abdomen brown, with a pair of white spots on the anterior third and two transverse median white stripes. Spinnerets black.
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="E21C36DFA666FF894BA8BBC2BF79F915" blockId="6.[850,1475,1293,1790]" box="[911,1103,1770,1790]" pageId="6" pageNumber="145">Female. Unknown.</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
